# MemQ Memory Protocol — Cursor Rules

# Persistent Memory (MemQ MCP)
# You have access to persistent sovereign memory via MemQ MCP tools. USE THEM.

## Session Start
# Execute these IMMEDIATELY on every new conversation:
# 1. reunion(include_status: true) — Verify MemQ connection
# 2. recent_memory(limit: 10) — Load recent context
# 3. search_memory(query: "<current task>", top_k: 5) — Find relevant past work
# If unavailable: warn "⚠️ MemQ unavailable — degraded mode" and continue.

## During Work
# - Before planning: search_memory(query: "<topic>", top_k: 5)
# - After completing: add_memory(text: "<summary>", memory_type: "checkpoint", tags: ["<domain>"])
# - On bugs: add_memory(text: "<root cause + fix>", memory_type: "episodic", tags: ["bug"])
# - On discoveries: add_memory(text: "<learning>", memory_type: "semantic", tags: ["pattern"])
# - Context needed: mnemosyne_context(objective: "<goal>", include_recent: true)

## Session End
# reflect_memory(window: 50, force: true) — Consolidate learnings

## Memory Types
# episodic — Events and debugging ("Fixed timeout in webhook handler")
# semantic — Facts and patterns ("Auth uses HMAC-SHA256 with replay protection")
# procedural — Workflows ("Deploy: push master → CI → wrangler deploy")
# checkpoint — Completions ("Billing overhaul done: 7 files, tests pass")
# reflection — Meta-learning ("Auth bugs: check middleware first")
